{"id":1300,"date":"2011-01-14T05:06:18","date_gmt":"2011-01-14T11:06:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/follow-up_oprah_winfrey_network.php"},"modified":"2011-01-14T05:06:18","modified_gmt":"2011-01-14T11:06:18","slug":"follow_up_oprah_winfrey_network","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/follow_up_oprah_winfrey_network.php","title":{"rendered":"Follow-up: Oprah Winfrey Network"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/own_follow_up.jpg\" alt=\"Oprah Winfrey Network, Follow-up\"><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/the_many_layers_of_oprah.php\">Last October we reported on the new identity of OWN<\/a>, the Oprah Winfrey Network. I closed the post with this: &#8220;As with most TV identity reveals, we will have to wait to see how it evolves and how it animates. Expect a follow-up post in January 2011.&#8221; So, as prognosticated, here is the follow-up, now that the channel has been on the air for a few days. Philadelphia-based <a href=\"http:\/\/www.bigsmack.tv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Bigsmack<\/a> was in charge of designing the on-air package for OWN.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>Working off a logo designed by Bruce Mau Design, Chicago, the OWN on-air look conceptually takes viewers inside the &#8220;O&#8221; of the logo &mdash; a modern, warmly lit world that abstractly resembles the look of naturally blown glass combined with an array of organic elements and digital animation.<br \/><br \/>One of BIGSMACK&#8217;s notable contributions was the idea of color-coding the on-air elements for specific times of the day. In the morning, the look veers toward a palate of orange and yellow hues; while a green tint marks the afternoon; and cool purple and burgundy shades represent the evening hours.<br \/><br \/>&#8220;Using different colors gave us the freedom to explore the logo in different ways,&#8221; says Hann, who presented the BIGSMACK pitch directly to Winfrey and her team. &#8220;We chose to present the logo as a sculpture, a piece of crystal art that grabs viewer&#8217;s attention and makes a statement, giving the mark a feeling of importance. Going inside the &#8216;O&#8217; is a metaphor for journey, personal growth, and awakenings, which is what Oprah is all about.&#8221;<br \/>Bigsmack Press Release<\/blockquote>\n<p>The release also offers confirmation that Bruce Mau Design created the logo, although not in its final form:<\/p>\n<blockquote>Hann also noted that the Bruce Mau Design logo was the most complicated he had ever worked with. &#8220;We were given a 2D logo, but the OWN crew wanted it to be interpreted into 3D. It ended up being a complicated model that made for long render times. For a network package, this was a significantly more complex logo than most.&#8221;<\/blockquote>\n<br \/>\n<script src=\"http:\/\/www.apple.com\/library\/quicktime\/scripts\/ac_quicktime.js\" language=\"JavaScript\" type=\"text\/javascript\"><\/script>\n<script src=\"http:\/\/www.apple.com\/library\/quicktime\/scripts\/qtp_library.js\" language=\"JavaScript\" type=\"text\/javascript\"><\/script>\n<link href=\"http:\/\/www.apple.com\/library\/quicktime\/stylesheets\/qtp_library.css\" rel=\"StyleSheet\" type=\"text\/css\" \/>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\"><!--\n\tQT_WritePoster_XHTML('Click to Play', 'https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE_small.jpg',\n\t\t'https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE.m4v',\n\t\t'574', '325', '',\n\t\t'controller', 'true',\n\t\t'autoplay', 'true',\n\t\t'bgcolor', 'white',\n\t\t'scale', 'aspect');\n\/\/-->\n<\/script>\n<noscript>\n<object width=\"574\" height=\"325\" classid=\"clsid:02BF25D5-8C17-4B23-BC80-D3488ABDDC6B\" codebase=\"http:\/\/www.apple.com\/qtactivex\/qtplugin.cab\">\n\t<param name=\"src\" value=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE_small.jpg\" \/>\n\t<param name=\"href\" value=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE.m4v\" \/>\n\t<param name=\"target\" value=\"myself\" \/>\n\t<param name=\"controller\" value=\"false\" \/>\n\t<param name=\"autoplay\" value=\"false\" \/>\n\t<param name=\"scale\" value=\"aspect\" \/>\n\t<embed width=\"574\" height=\"325\" type=\"video\/quicktime\" pluginspage=\"http:\/\/www.apple.com\/quicktime\/download\/\"\n\t\tsrc=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE_small.jpg\"\n\t\thref=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE.m4v\"\n\t\ttarget=\"myself\"\n\t\tcontroller=\"false\"\n\t\tautoplay=\"false\"\n\t\tscale=\"aspect\">\n\t<\/embed>\n<\/object>\n<\/noscript>\n<br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\">See bigger version <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/OWN_MONTAGE.m4v\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>In the logo review I mentioned I liked the logo. Not loved it. Just liked it. The animations really help give it the necessary flair to make the static version relevant. And more than blown glass I see animated hard candy. A good thing. The animations have a lick-ability factor lacking in many of today&#8217;s on-air packages. Also a good thing. I think. Either way, the flamboyance of the on-air work is perfectly suited for the network.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110114_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110114_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\",